result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Terry William Fremling

records.addlTxt:
10:42 AM Defendant Terry William Fremling in court.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Court notes defendant does not have attorney. State calls witness, Samuel Finkbeiner, Officer, City of Superior PD. Witness sworn and testifies. State-direct examination of witness. October 27, 2022, City of Superior, Douglas County Wisconsin. Witness identifies Defendant. Record reflects identification. Defendant has no questions for witness. Court questions witness. State rests. 
State makes argument for bind over. Defendant has nothing to say.  Court finds probable cause and binds the Defendant over for Arraignment. 
Court reminds the Defendant of their bail conditions. Defendant orally confirms they have received date and time of hearing and confirms they will attend. Defendant provided notice.
Arraignment scheduled for December 27, 2022 at 09:30 am.

records.descr: Pet for appointment counsel,affidavit of indigency

records.addlTxt:
4:10 PM Defendant Terry William Fremling in court.  Attorney Angela Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant indicates that he does not have an attorney yet.  Tried to contact the public defenders office and couldn't get through. His boss looked on the computer and called a different number. Defendant does not qualify for public defender.
Court questions intent. Defendant intends to apply for a court appointed attorney.
Defendant wishes to waive time limits for preliminary hearing to be able to obtain counsel.
Court accepts waiver as knowing and voluntary.  Resets PH.
State has no objection.
Court informs defendant that he may not qualify but directs defendant to apply.  Court calculates based on income and lets defendant know that he makes too much to qualify for court appointed attorney but that he can still apply if he wishes.
State requests hearing be set out to November.
Court reminds of bail/conditions. 
Court removes preliminary hearing from the calendar this wednesday.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for November 2, 2022 at 10:45 am.
No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription. No operation of a motor vehicle unless Defendant has valid permit or license.

1:40 PM Defendant Terry William Fremling appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Ryan Reid in court with Defendant. Attorney Angela Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case. Address verified. Attorney Reid acknowledges receipt, waives reading, pleads not guilty to misdemeanors. Court accepts plea.
State requests $250 cash, no drugs, no driving without valid permit or license. Cites priors and 4 prior FTA's. 
Attorney Reid asks for signature bond or lower cash bond. Has given Superior address. 
Court orders $1,000 cash, with conditions of no use or possession of drugs or drug paraphernalia without valid prescription, no operation of vehicle without valid license or permit.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 28, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Status conference scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
